# MCR 418: Materials Counts (1) - Data Prep

**Date Posted:** June 22, 2026

## Overview

This query is the first of four queries used to support annual materials count reporting. It creates the underlying data preparation table that serves as the foundation for subsequent materials count processing and reporting.

## Query Sequence

### 1. MCR 418 — Materials Counts (1): Data Prep
Creates the underlying data preparation table based on MARC bibliographic and holdings data.

### 2. MCR 419 — Primary Formats
Builds the primary formats table by applying format classification logic to the data preparation table created in MCR 418.

### 3. MCR 420 — Flattened Formats
Creates a flattened version of the primary formats table to facilitate counting and reporting. This step is necessary because the primary formats table contains array-based fields that are not conducive to straightforward aggregation.

### 4. MCR 421 — Materials Counts
Generates the final materials counts used for annual reporting. This query can be modified as needed to support specific reporting requirements.

## Workflow

MCR 418 (Data Prep)
        ↓
MCR 419 (Primary Formats)
        ↓
MCR 420 (Flattened Formats)
        ↓
MCR 421 (Materials Counts)
